# Token Budget Rules

This project runs on a limited token budget. Follow these rules to avoid waste.

## Agent Usage
- **Review mode: solo** — do NOT auto-spawn code-reviewer or security-reviewer agents unless explicitly asked
- Only use `Task` subagents when the work genuinely requires parallel exploration or specialist knowledge
- Prefer doing work directly over delegating to subagents for tasks under ~50 lines of change
- When a subagent IS needed, prefer `model: fast` unless deep reasoning is required

## Efficiency
- Read files before editing — never guess at file contents
- Batch related edits into single tool calls where possible
- Don't re-read files you've already read in this session unless they've changed
- Validate with headless Godot (`--quit-after 3`) instead of spinning up full editor sessions
- Keep commit messages concise — no multi-paragraph descriptions

## What NOT to Auto-Run
- No automatic code reviews after every change
- No automatic security scans
- No automatic documentation generation
- No automatic test generation (until test framework is set up)
- Ask before running expensive operations (full codebase search, multi-agent workflows)
